CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 27, 1957, pg. A18, reads: "Visitor Feted - Mrs. Samuel J. Wynn (second from left) entertained last Saturday afternoon in honor of her house guest, Mrs. Harry Parker of Washington, D. C. The hostess and her guest are surrounded by attractive aides who helped serve the many guests who came to greet the visitor at the charming Wynn home. Left to right: Mmes. Arthur Wray, Wynn, Parker, James Dugan, Abram T. Hall and Murrell [Murrel] Wynn Jones, daughter of the hostess. Standing in the rear, Mrs. Barbara Jones Clark, granddaughter of the hostess, and Mrs. Charles Hamilton. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Arthur Wray, Mrs. Samuel J. Wynn, Mrs. Harry Parker, Mrs. James Dugan, Mrs. Abram T. Hall, Murrel Wynn Jones, and Barbara Jones Clark and Mrs. Charles Hamilton standing in back, posed in front of Wynn home
